The line below is needed for doxygen documentation
//! [highlandIO.parameters.dat_flattree]


Set the config manually 
-1 (less than 0) - read from input,
if fails to read from input then the one corresponding to the production version
used to compile highland will be used: e.g. prod8* - ND280Upgrade, prod7* -ND280
One rarely expects to set manually the flag to the exact production - is kept
for some debugging purposes
0 - nd280, 
1 (more than 0) - upgrade
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.Config = -1 >

Save the Geometry (TGeoManager)
 < highlandIO.FlatTree.SaveGeometry = 1 >
 
 
 
 March 2020 - Prod6T sand muons, water out -- whether to set manually POT per spill 
 and the very POT per spill
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.SetManual_POTPerSpill_Prod6T_WaterOut_Sand = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.POTPerSpill_Prod6T_WaterOut_Sand           = 9.4804e13 >



FGD individual hits info: i.e. setting it to save FGD hits on flat-tree creation
level and with the oaAnalysis input will automatically force oaAnalysis
converter to fill the corresponding hits info

 < highlandIO.FlatTree.Read.TimeBins.FGD.FillHits = 0 >
 < highlandIO.FlatTree.Create.TimeBins.FGD.SaveHits = 0 >

Ignore true vertices that have all true tracks contained in a given subdetector
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreSMRDContainedTrueObjects      = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreDsECalContainedTrueObjects    = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreBrECalContainedTrueObjects    = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreP0DECalContainedTrueObjects   = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreINGRIDContainedTrueObjects    = 0 >

Ignore true vertices with no true tracks
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.RemoveTrueVerticesWithNoTrueParticles  = 1 >

Shuts up the message and stops early exit if
subsequent files have colliding run numbers.
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.ForceIgnoreRunNumberClash = 0 >

Ignore bad data quality flags due to P0D off T2K run14
If P0D is the only cause the global DQ will be set to good
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.IgnoreP0DOffInRun14BadDQFlag = 1 >

Controls whether to add single hits into time bins
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.TimeBins.FGD.FillHits = 1 > // FGD
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.TimeBins.SFG.FillHits = 1 > // SFG

Controls whether to add single hit and nodes for SFG objects

 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.Particles.SFG.FillHits = 1 > 
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.Particles.SFG.FillNodes = 1 > 


Controls for oa/eventAnalysis skimming

 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.CherryPicker.UseTPC = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.CherryPicker.UseFGD = 0 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.CherryPicker.UseSFG = 1 >
 < highlandIO.oaAnalysis.CherryPicker.UseHAT = 0 >

